{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1964 |Team=Indiana Hoosiers |Image= |Conference=Big Ten Conference |ShortConference=Big Ten |Record=2-7-0 |ConfRecord=1-5-0 |CoachRank= |APRank= |HeadCoach=[[Phil Dickens]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Memorial Stadium, Bloomington|Memorial Stadium]] |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{1964 Big Ten football standings}} The '''1964 Indiana Hoosiers football team''' represented [[Indiana University]] in the [[1964 college football season]]. The Hoosiers offense scored 154 points while the defense allowed 188 points.
==Season== *In the [[Old Oaken Bucket]], the Hoosiers lost to Purdue by a score of 22-28.
